<font color="#FF0000">STILL SEARCHING- ALWAYS SHALL!</font><br>
<tt>Fri Nov  7 21:20:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
For Anne, Class Lass and my BOCs<br><br>
&quot;Endless Patrol&quot;<br><br>
In long wet shadows, like specters they float,<br>
when the morning sun begins to rise.<br>
Ghostly men in tiger stripes and boonie hats,<br>
with paint around their eyes.<br><br>
Like vapor they ebb, not trembling the leaves<br>
nor making a single perceptible sound.<br>
Drifting silently, as a green mirage they flow<br>
through dangerous and treacherous ground.<br><br>
With each man in trail, they journey along<br>
where hardly a trail dares to exist.<br>
They move, then pause and move again<br>
to be swallowed by the mountain mist.<br><br>
Where do they come from and where are they going<br>
in the murky labyrinth of my troubled mind?<br>
Are they seeking answers to why so many died, <br>
searching for reasons they never shall find?<br><br>
Scouting, quietly, the broken perimeter,<br>
bent upon breeching the gap and rift,<br>
They recognize the perilous straits,<br>
through which they persistently drift.<br><br>
But...they will never surrender,<br>
they will continue the endless patrol,<br>
forever occupying my bleeding heart;<br>
...forever guarding my shattered soul.<br><br>
From &quot;Scars and Stripes, Forever&quot; Copywrite 1990 E Ramon<br><br>
MTF
<p><code>-- combat brothers  (never forsake you) </code><p>


